statement.markdown:
heading: Responsive Search Bar
content: Create a search bar that is fully responsive. The search bar should have a text input and a search button. The search bar should take up 100% of the width on small screens (max-width: 767px) and 30% of the width on medium to large screens (max-width: 1023px). On extra large screens (max-width: not set), it should take up 20% of the width. When the screen size is extra large, the search bar should be positioned to the right. It should also have a hover effect that changes the background color of the button to #4CAF50.
requirements
{"number":1,"description":"Use Tailwind CSS for styling."}
{"number":2,"description":"Use HTML and CSS to create the search bar."}
{"number":3,"description":"Make sure the search bar takes up 100% of the width on small screens."}
{"number":4,"description":"On medium to large screens, the search bar should take up 30% of the width."}
{"number":5,"description":"On extra large screens, the search bar should take up 20% of the width."}
{"number":6,"description":"On extra large screens, the search bar should be positioned to the right."}
{"number":7,"description":"Add a hover effect to the search button that changes the background color to #4CAF50."}
